rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of electrical current collectors. These are the parts of electric locomotives, trams, or trolleybuses that lead electrical power from powers sources to the electrical parts of the vehicles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Electrical Current Collector

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for locomotive classes that use diesel fuel.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Diesel Locomotive Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.diesel_locomotive_class to the locomotive's engine that converts the fuel to work. It is the source of power for propulsion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Prime Mover

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for locomotive classes that are powered by electricity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Electric Locomotive Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.electric_locomotive_class to its collection method for the electrical current.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Current Collection Method

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.electric_locomotive_class to a standard descriptor for its electrical system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Electric System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains standard descriptors for the electrical systems used by railways, providing the voltage and indicating whether they use direct or alternating current.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Electric System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a standard descriptor for an electric system with a type of locomotive that is compatible with the system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all locomotives. Locomotives are the railway vehicles that provide the power for an mso:rail.train.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive to the date when the process of building the locomotive started.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Construction Begun

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive to the date when the process of building the locomotive ended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Construction Completed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive to its first run date, the date the locomotive first ran on a railway line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Run Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive to the date of its last run. This is the date the locomotive made its last run on its railway line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Last Run Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a locomotive to the corresponding locomotive class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive Class
Owners
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:event.agent.owner instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:event.agent.owner]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive to its order number.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Order Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive to its serial number.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Serial Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive to its status information, which includes things like operational, scrapped, or refitted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of brakes used in locomotives.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive Brakes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing companies that specialize in manufacturing locomotives.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive Builder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a locomotive manufacturer to a locomotive class that the manufacturer was or is responsible for building.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive Classes Built

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for locomotive classes, e.g. British Rail Class 73.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the AAR wheel arrangement, which is a classification of locomotive wheel arrangements developed by the Association of American Railroads.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: AAR Wheel Arrangement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the method of mixing fuel and air the locomotive's engine uses.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aspiration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the assigned axle load class for the locomotive class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Axle Load Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the force the brakes supply.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Brake Force

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the type of brakes available on the locomotive for this class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Brakes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the builder's model number for the class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Model

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the size of the cylinders used in the engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cylinder Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the mso:event.agent that designed the class of locomotive.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the volume swept away by all the pistons inside the cylinders. This measurement does not include the total volume of the combustion chamber.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Displacement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the type of engine used in its locomotives. Note mso:engineering.engine_type is deprecated, and this expected type will change to mso:engineering.engine_category in the future.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Engine Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the frame size information. The frame is the structure for the locomotive and supports the other elements like the boiler and cab.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Frame Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to its full fuel capacity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fuel Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the type of fuel used by locomotives in this class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fuel Used

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to the measurement of the tracks in millimeters on which locomotives of this class can run.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gauge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to the height in meters of locomotives of this class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Height

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to the date that locomotives of this class were first used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Introduced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to the length in meters of locomotives of this class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the locale(s) in which instances of the class operated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locale

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to specific instances of this class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to the company that manufactured the class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive Builder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to information about which railway operators used the locomotive class and when. Note that the expected type of this property should eventually be changed to common.operator_relationship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Used by

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the weight of its locomotives, without tender weight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive Weight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the maximum load its axles can bear.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Axle Load

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to the maximum speed in kilometers per hour of locomotives of this class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the minimum curve radius for the class. This radius has design implications for railways.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Curve Radius

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the other types of locomotive it can be coupled with and used under the control of one driver.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Multiple Working

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class the the number of cylinders, or its piston configuration for the engine used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cylinders

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to a standard descriptor for the type of track on which the locomotive class can run.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gauge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the mso:rail.railway on which locomotives of this class ran or run currently.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railroad(s)

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to its engine's Revolutions per Minute range. RPMs measures the frequency of a rotation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: RPM Range

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the safety information, include types of safety systems, installed on engines of this class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Safety

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the status information for the class, which includes things like operational, scrapped, or refitted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the total power output of its engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Power Output

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the number of locomotives produced in this class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Production Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the tractive effort, the force generated by the engine to generate motion, of its engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tractive Effort

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to information about the train's heating system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Train Heating

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the mso:automotive.transmission that is used in the engine for the class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Transmission

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to standard designation of its wheel arrangement.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: UIC Classification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the type of valve used in the engine of the locomotive class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Valve Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to the weight in tonnes of locomotives of this class including any tenders.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to its wheel diameter, if the class has wheels that are uniform in diameter. Please see mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class.leading_wheel_diameter, mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class.driving_wheel_diameter, and mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class.trailing_wheel_diameter for more specific properties when the types of wheels are different sizes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wheel Diameter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the wheelbase measurement for the class. This measurement is taken between the points where the locomotive's wheels contact the rails.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wheelbase

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to the width in meters of locomotives of this class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Width

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a locomotive class to the date that locomotives of this class were last used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Withdrawn

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for kinds of track gauge, e.g. standard gauge, narrow gauge, and broad gauge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rail Gauge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a standard descriptor for a type of railroad gauge to the maximum width in millimeters of tracks that have this gauge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Width

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a standard descriptor for a type of railroad gauge to the minimum width in millimeters of tracks that have this gauge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minimum Width

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a standard descriptor for a railroad gauge to a railway that uses this gauge.

Rail network

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railways in this network
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a railway to the date that the railway ceased operations.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Closed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Line Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.railway to the maximum speed allowed on the railway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.railway to the number of stations along the railway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a railway to the date that the railway began operations.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Opened

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a railway to information about the company that manages the railway and when. Note that the expected type of this property should eventually be changed to common.operator_relationship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a railway to information about the gauge of track used on the railway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gauge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a railway to an endpoint of the railway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Terminus

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a railway to information about the locomotives used by the railway and when they were used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rolling Stock

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.railway to the total length of track for the railway. This total includes yard lines and the other tacks not used for main line or branch lines.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Track Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing bridges that are used primarily or exclusively for carrying trains.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railway Bridge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property indicating whether or not the railway bridge is electrified.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Electrified

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a railway bridge to a number indicating how many railway tracks run across the bridge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Tracks

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a railway bridge to information about the gauge of track that runs across the bridge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rail Gauge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the gauges of tracks on a railway and the dates when the railway had the gauges.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railway-gauge Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date from which the railway had the specified gauge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the gauge of the track itself.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gauge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the railway about which gauge information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railway

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date to which the railway had the specified gauge.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To Date
Width

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.railway_locomotive_class_relationship to the mso:rail.locomotive_class in the relationship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.railway_locomotive_class_relationship to the number of locomotives of the given class the railway operates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.railway_locomotive_class_relationship to the operating number for locomotives in the class assigned by the railway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railroad Operating Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.railway_locomotive_class_relationship to the class the railway assigned locomotives of this class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railroad Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.railway_locomotive_class_relationship to the mso:rail.railway in the relationship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railway

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A company that manages a railway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railway Operator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a railway operator to information about the locomotive classes that are used by the railway operator.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive Classes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a railway operator to information about the railways managed by the company and when they were managed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railways

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An end point for a railway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railway Terminus

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a railway station to a three-letter code assigned by the International Air Transport Association to identify the station. Note that many railway stations with IATA codes are part of airports, but not all of them are.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: IATA

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a railway terminus to railway that begins or ends at the terminus.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railways Terminating Here

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for kinds of railways, e.g. military railway, heritage railway, and industrial railway.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a standard descriptor for a type of railway to information about specific railways that are instances of this type.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the classification of railways and when they were so classified.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date from which the given railway was an instance of the given railway type.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the given railway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Railway

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the date until which the given locomotive was used by the given railway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for locomotive classes that are powered by steam.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Steam Locomotive Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a steam locomotive class to the number of components that convert steam power into motion.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cylinders

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class to the diameter of the driving wheels, which are the powered wheels driven by the locomotive's pistons.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Driving Wheel Diameter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a steam locomotive class to a number indicating the weight on the driving wheels divided by the starting tractive effort.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class to the total heating surface, including tubes and flues, for the class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Heating Surface

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Proeprty relating an mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class to the surface area of its tubes. These are the tubes located in the engine's broiler.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tube Heating Surface

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class to the combines heating surface area of the tubes and flues for the class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tubes And Flues Heating Surface

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the diameter of its leading wheels. The leading wheels are the unpowered wheel(s) located on the front of the locomotive in front of the driving wheels.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Leading Wheel Diameter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The wheel configuration in Whyte notation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wheel configuration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.locomotive_class to the weight of the locomotive tender.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tender Weight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Proeprty relating an mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class to the diameter of its trailing wheels. These are the typically unpowered wheels located behind the driving wheels on steam locomotives.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trailing Wheel Diameter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class to the type of valve gear used by the class. Valve gears are those mechanisms on a steam engine that operate the inlet and exhaust valves.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Valve Gear

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Proeprty relating an mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class to its tender's full water capacity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Water Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.steam_locomotive_class to the weight the driving wheels bear. These wheels are the powered middle wheels on a steam engine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weight On Drivers
Steam locomotive fuel type
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use mso:automotive.fuel instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:automotive.fuel ]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: used_by
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard configurations of steam locomotives in Whyte notation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Steam Locomotive Wheel Configuration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a standard descriptor for a steam locomotive wheel configuration to a locomotive class that has this wheel configuration.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locomotive Classes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all trains. Trains are the vehicles in rail transport consisting of at least one mso:rail.locomotive and a series of railroad cars carrying passengers or cargo.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Train

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to its rate of acceleration.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Acceleration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to the mso:engineering.material(s) that makes up its car body.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Car Body

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to the length of one of its cars.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Car Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to its rate of deceleration.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Deceleration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to its dimensions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dimensions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to its floor height, which is the height of the floor of the cars of the train above the rail.
Property relating an mso:rail.train to information about its formation, typically the number of cars in each possible trainset, e.g. "4 cars per trainset" or "3, 6, and 9 cars."
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Formation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to its assigned maintenance depot. These are the depots were the trains are serviced.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Depot

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to its permitted maximum speed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to the number of doors that each car has.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number Doors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to the total number of trains still in service across all railways.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number in Service
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to rail.railway. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to the total number of trains scrapped across all railways.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number Scrapped
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to rail.railway. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating an mso:rail.train to the mso:common.operator_relationship that collects operating data for the train.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operated

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to the number of passengers the train can carry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Capacity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Proeprty relating an mso:rail.train to the manufacturer's family or product line of which the train is a part.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Family

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to the mso:rail.railway on which the train runs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an replacement mso:rail.train to the previously manufactured mso:rail.train the former replaced.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Replaced

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to the time interval of the train's service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Service Start

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to its track guage, which is the spacing of the rails on a track.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Track Gauge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to its classification of axle arrangement according to the International Union of Railways.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: UIC Classification of locomotive axle arrangements

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:rail.train to its weight. This is the total weight of the locomotive and its cars.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A service involving trains along a fixed route with established stops, e.g. the Starlight Express and Acela Express offered by Amtrak.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Train Line

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the average speed, in kilometers per hour, of trains running on the line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Average Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the average amount of time, in minutes, for a train on the line to travel between the origin station and the destination station.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Average Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to a standard descriptor for a baggage option offered by the line, e.g. overhead bins, luggage racks, no checked luggage, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baggage Option

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the date when the line started operating.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Began Operation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the city where the line ends.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Destination City

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the railway station where the line ends.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Destination Station

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to a standard descriptor for a dining option offered by the line, e.g. on-board caf?? and at-seat meals in first class.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dining Option

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether the given train line has made provisions for people with special needs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Disabled

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the distance, in Kilometers, travelled from the origin station to the destination station.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the date, if any, that the line ceased operating.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ended Operation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the maximum speed, in kilometers per hour, of trains running on the line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Maximum Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the maximum number of stops that the line makes. Note that different train services operating on the line may make different stops, depending on whether they are local or express services.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Stops

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the operator of the train line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Operator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the city where the line begins.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Origin City

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the railway station where the line begins.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Origin Station

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a train line to a defunct line that previously offered the same sort of service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Predecessor Train Line

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to a standard descriptor for the kind of track gauge, e.g. standard gauge, narrow gauge, and broad gauge, along which the train line runs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rail Gauge

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a train line to the region where the train line operates, e.g. the Northeastern United States.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Region

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to the number of people who travelled on the line in a given calendar or financial year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ridership

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to a standard descriptor for a seating class offered by the line, e.g. coach, business class, first class, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Seating Class

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to a standard descriptor for a seating configuration offered by the line, e.g. reclining leather seats, four across in business class, three across in first class, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Seating Configuration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to a standard descriptor for the train line, e.g. "high speed tilting train".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Service Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a defunct train line to a line that later offered the same sort of service as the defunct line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Successor Train Line

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a train line to the average number of trains per day that run as part of the line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Train Frequency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to one of the alphanumeric identifiers for train services that are part of the line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Train Numbers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train line to a train service that is part of the line.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Train Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A particular instance of a train serving on an mso:rail.train_line. For example, the Acela Express operates 20 trains per day, and each of these trains serving on this line would be an instance of mso:rail.train_service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Train Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train service to an alphanumeric identifier for the train service.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train service to one of the scheduled stops that the service makes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stops

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A scheduled stop made by an instance of mso:rail.train_service operating on a particular mso:rail.train_line. A stop is defined by the scheduled arrival and departure times, as well as the station where the stop is made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Train Service Stop

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a scheduled stop to the time when the train is slated to arrive at the stop.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Arrival Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a scheduled stop to the time when the train is slated to leave the stop.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Departure Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a train service stop to the station where the stop is made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Station
